3. LICENSE VALIDATION  ← please read

   The Software includes an automated license-validation mechanism.  By
   installing or using the Software you expressly consent to the following:

   a. PERIODIC NETWORK CHECK
      At randomised intervals (approximately every 1–15 minutes while the
      Software is running) the Software contacts the following URL to verify
      that this installation is authorised:

        https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rhshourav/HydraCast
            /****

      No personally identifiable information is transmitted; the Software
      only reads a short validation token from that URL.

   b. FAILURE COUNTER
      If the validation server is reachable but returns an unexpected token,
      a failure is recorded locally.  Network errors (server unreachable,
      no Internet connection) do NOT count as failures.

   c. PERMANENT LOCK
      After ten (10) confirmed validation failures the Software will write
      a lock file to:

        <your home directory>/.hydracast/installation.lock

      Once locked, the Software will refuse to start and will display a
      message directing you to the author.  The lock persists until the
      author issues an unlock or you reinstall under a valid license.

   d. RENEWAL
      To renew or restore a locked installation contact the author at:

        https://github.com/rhshourav/HydraCast

